### F5OS Tenants API – REST Client Examples
# Assumes VS Code REST Client (humao.rest-client) is installed.
#
# Set environment variables in your REST client environment settings
# for {{f5os_host}}, {{f5os_user}}, {{f5os_pass}} as appropriate, or replace
# them inline.

@f5os_host = 10.0.0.10
@auth_basic = Basic {{base64 f5os_user:f5os_pass}}

### List all tenants
GET https://{{f5os_host}}/restconf/data/f5-tenants:tenants
Authorization: {{auth_basic}}
Accept: application/yang-data+json

###
### Create tenant1 (BIG-IP)
POST https://{{f5os_host}}/restconf/data/f5-tenants:tenants
Authorization: {{auth_basic}}
Content-Type: application/yang-data+json
Accept: application/yang-data+json

{
  "f5-tenants:tenant": [
    {
      "config": {
        "f5-tenants:name": "tenant1",
        "f5-tenants:type": "BIG-IP",
        "f5-tenants:mgmt-ip": "192.0.2.10",
        "f5-tenants:prefix-length": 24,
        "f5-tenants:gateway": "192.0.2.1",
        "f5-tenants:vlans": [
          "vlan-10"
        ],
        "f5-tenant-mgmt-vlan:mgmt-vlan": "mgmt-vlan"
      }
    }
  ]
}

###
### Show tenant1
GET https://{{f5os_host}}/restconf/data/f5-tenants:tenants/tenant=tenant1
Authorization: {{auth_basic}}
Accept: application/yang-data+json

###
### Update tenant1 management IP
PATCH https://{{f5os_host}}/restconf/data/f5-tenants:tenants/tenant=tenant1/config
Authorization: {{auth_basic}}
Content-Type: application/yang-data+json
Accept: application/yang-data+json

{
  "f5-tenants:mgmt-ip": "192.0.2.11",
  "f5-tenants:prefix-length": 24,
  "f5-tenants:gateway": "192.0.2.1"
}

###
### Delete tenant1
DELETE https://{{f5os_host}}/restconf/data/f5-tenants:tenants/tenant=tenant1
Authorization: {{auth_basic}}
Accept: application/yang-data+json

